-- Iran, India Agree to Settle Oil Bills in Rupees, Reuters Reports
-- B y   G r a n t   S m i t h
-- 2012-01-20T16:48:40Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-20/iran-india-agree-to-settle-oil-bills-in-rupees-reuters-reports.html
Iran  and India have agreed that some
of their $12 billion annual trade in oil can be settled in
rupees, to avoid restrictions posed by U.S. sanctions,  Reuters
said , citing a government official it didn’t identify.  Iran’s central bank will open an account with an Indian
lender to receive partial payment for the 400,000 barrels of
crude it exports a day to the Asian nation, Reuters said. UCO
Bank in India may be chosen, according to the  news agency .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Grant Smith in London at 
